personalInfo.fullAddress: Bole Road, Behind Edna Mall, Building 5, Apt 302, Addis Ababa
personalInfo.aboutYou: I am a passionate coffee enthusiast and cultural ambassador with over 15 years of experience hosting guests in my home. I grew up learning the traditional Ethiopian coffee ceremony from my grandmother and I love sharing this beautiful ritual with visitors from around the world.

experienceDetails.previousExperience: I have been hosting coffee ceremonies for tourists for over 10 years. I started by offering free ceremonies to friends and their visiting families, and it grew from there. I've hosted hundreds of guests from over 30 countries and received excellent feedback on platforms like TripAdvisor and Airbnb Experiences.

personalInfo.fullAddress: Yeka Sub-City, Gerji Area, House No. 245, Addis Ababa
personalInfo.aboutYou: I am a professional chef specializing in Ethiopian cuisine with 20 years of experience. I run cooking classes from my home kitchen and love teaching people about our rich culinary traditions. Making injera is an art form, and I'm excited to share the secrets and techniques passed down through generations.

experienceDetails.previousExperience: I worked as a head chef at several renowned Ethiopian restaurants in Addis Ababa for 15 years before starting my own cooking school. I've taught over 500 students, both locals and internationals, the art of Ethiopian cooking. I'm certified by the Ethiopian Culinary Association and have appeared on local cooking shows.

personalInfo.fullAddress: Kazanchis Area, Behind Commercial Bank of Ethiopia, Studio 12, Addis Ababa
personalInfo.aboutYou: I am a master artisan specializing in traditional Ethiopian basket weaving. I learned this craft from my mother and grandmother, who were both renowned weavers in our village. I moved to Addis Ababa 10 years ago and opened my studio to preserve and share this beautiful traditional art form.

experienceDetails.previousExperience: I have been weaving baskets for over 25 years and teaching workshops for 8 years. My work has been featured in several Ethiopian cultural exhibitions and I've sold pieces to collectors worldwide. I've taught hundreds of students and my workshops are highly rated on social media and travel blogs.

personalInfo.fullAddress: Lideta Sub-City, Near Piazza, Family Compound, House 45, Addis Ababa
personalInfo.aboutYou: I am a traditional Ethiopian musician and dance instructor with my family. Music and dance have been in our family for four generations. I play the krar, masinko, and kebero, and I love teaching the energetic eskista dance. Our family has performed at cultural festivals across Ethiopia.

experienceDetails.previousExperience: I've been performing and teaching traditional Ethiopian music and dance for 18 years. My family and I have hosted cultural evenings for tourists for the past 6 years. We've performed at the Ethiopian Cultural Center, various hotels, and private events. I've taught over 300 international visitors the basics of our traditional dances.

personalInfo.fullAddress: Arada Sub-City, Near Merkato, Traditional House, Gate 7, Addis Ababa
personalInfo.aboutYou: I am a storyteller and cultural educator with a deep love for Ethiopian traditions. I grew up listening to stories from my elders and learned the art of tea ceremonies from my family. I've been sharing our cultural heritage with visitors for years, creating meaningful connections through tea and conversation.

experienceDetails.previousExperience: I've been hosting tea ceremonies and storytelling sessions for 12 years. I've worked with cultural centers, schools, and tourism agencies to promote Ethiopian traditions. I've hosted over 400 guests and received recognition from the Ethiopian Tourism Organization for my contributions to cultural preservation.
